<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E5DFFD348A754A9FCABFA2D" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418E5DFFD348A754A9FD1AFB69" blockId="19.[150,1437,901,1790]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E5DFFD348A754A9FE38FC6E" bold="true" box="[151,413,901,926]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Description of female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E5DFFD3498154A9FDB3FC6D" box="[433,534,901,925]" captionStart="PLATE 5" captionStartId="15.[151,233,2013,2036]" captionTargetBox="[360,1218,190,1964]" captionTargetId="figure-37@15.[342,1245,175,1989]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="PLATE 5. Aphelopus alebroides. A. Female. Length 1.7 mm. B. Male. Length 1.8 mm. (From Xu et al. 2011c)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278386" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278386/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Plate 5A</figureCitation>
). Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48E5DFFD34B1B54A9FC1CFC6D" box="[811,953,901,925]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.6">1.6–1.9 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible testaceous; antenna brown, except segments 1–3 testaceous; mesosoma black; metasoma brown; legs testaceous. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 6:6:6:7:8:7:7:7:6.5:11.5. Head dull, granulated; frontal line complete; POL = 9; OL = 6; OOL = 4; OPL = 3; TL = 3; greatest breadth of posterior ocelli about as long as OPL; occipital carina complete. Scutum, scutellum and metanotum dull, granulated. Notauli incomplete, reaching about 0.3–0.5 length of scutum. Propodeum with anterior surface reticulate rugose; posterior surface sculptured by two longitudinal keels, lateral areas dull, reticulate rugose and median area shiny and smooth. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418E5DFFD348F75389FCABFA2D" blockId="19.[150,1437,901,1790]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E5DFFD348F75389FE16FB4D" bold="true" box="[199,435,1189,1214]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Description of male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E5DFFD349F65389FD82FB4D" box="[454,551,1189,1213]" captionStart="PLATE 5" captionStartId="15.[151,233,2013,2036]" captionTargetBox="[360,1218,190,1964]" captionTargetId="figure-37@15.[342,1245,175,1989]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="PLATE 5. Aphelopus alebroides. A. Female. Length 1.7 mm. B. Male. Length 1.8 mm. (From Xu et al. 2011c)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278386" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278386/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Plate 5B</figureCitation>
). Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48E5DFFD34B065389FC64FB4D" box="[822,961,1189,1213]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="1.7" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.6">1.6–1.8 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible testaceous; antenna brown, except segments 1–2 testaceous; mesosoma black; metasoma brown; legs testaceous. Antenna filiform; antennal segments in following proportions: 5.5:5.5:7:9:9:12:12:12:11:17. Head dull, granulated; frontal line complete; POL = 12; OL = 6; OOL = 4; OPL = 2.5; TL = 2.5; greatest breadth of posterior ocelli slightly longer than OPL (3:2.5); occipital carina complete. Scutum, scutellum and metanotum dull, granulated. Notauli incomplete, reaching about 0.3–0.5 length of scutum. Propodeum with anterior surface reticulate rugose; posterior surface sculptured by two longitudinal keels, lateral areas dull, reticulate rugose and median area shiny and smooth. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands. Basivolsella fused with paramere, without outer basal process, with two subdistal bristles (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E5DFFD349FC52E9FD89FA2D" box="[460,556,1477,1501]" captionStart="PLATE 6" captionStartId="17.[151,233,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[196,1404,192,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-101@17.[151,1436,157,1936]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="PLATE 6. A–C, E–G.Male genitalia. A. Aphelopus achterbergi, holotype (from Olmi 1998a). B. A. albiclypeus from Laos. C. A. alebroides, holotype (from Xu et al. 2011c). D. Arboridia sp. parasitized by A. alebroides (from Xu et al. 2011c). E. A. borneanus from China. F. A. indicus, holotype (from Olmi 2010). G. A. luteoceps, holotype. Scale bar 0.18 mm for A, 0.16 mm for B, 0.14 mm for C, E and F, 0.26 mm for G." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278390" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278390/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Plate 6C</figureCitation>
). Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
